{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"eb0d5f3e-b535-4f09-adfd-5faea74a1920","content":"Run **`dotnet workload update`**.\n\n- **`dotnet workload update`** – downloads and installs the latest versions of all installed workloads, aligning them with your current SDK. This is what you want after an SDK update.\n- **`dotnet workload repair`** – reinstalls the *same* versions already recorded; it fixes corrupted installations but won't pull newer workload packages.\n\nAfter updating:\n\n```bash\ndotnet workload update\ndotnet build\n```\n\nIf you still see errors, check that the required workload is actually installed:\n\n```bash\ndotnet workload list\n```\n\nFor MAUI you need the `maui` workload (or `maui-android`, `maui-ios`, etc.). Install any missing ones with `dotnet workload install maui`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9a4de841-2695-41b3-9e34-e9dc820646ef","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the difference between `dotnet workload update` and `dotnet workload repair` to fix build issues after a .NET SDK update. This is a general knowledge question that I can answer directly without needing to look anything up.","outputTokens":253,"requestId":"6C1A:30221B:7B379C:83B14D:6A0AF5C2"},"id":"62c40c25-8b80-4835-9eba-1be7ab30118d","timestamp":"2026-05-18T11:19:39.318Z","parentId":"6fe10749-8002-46c3-a42e-72c3a611bda1"}
